model.content:
import requests
import json
import base64
# The cloud vision api returns RGB colours so had to turn them to some known solid ones
solid_colors = {
    "Black": (0, 0, 0),
    "White": (255, 255, 255),
    "Red": (255, 0, 0),
    "Green": (0, 255, 0),
    "Blue": (0, 0, 255),
    "Yellow": (255, 255, 0),
    "Cyan": (0, 255, 255),
    "Magenta": (255, 0, 255),
    "Gray": (128, 128, 128),
    "Maroon": (128, 0, 0),
    "Olive": (128, 128, 0),
    "Purple": (128, 0, 128),
    "Teal": (0, 128, 128),
    "Navy": (0, 0, 128)
}
ec_image = document.get_meta_data_value("ec_images")[0]
api_key = "AIzaSyD4On0UoxkQzo6iR8e0_NSH_H7m40QjX8s"
# Function to calculate the solid colours from RGB
def find_closest_color(rgb):
    closest_color_name = None
    min_distance = float('inf')
    for color_name, color_rgb in solid_colors.items():
        distance = ((rgb.get("red", 0) - color_rgb[0]) ** 2 +
                    (rgb.get("green", 0) - color_rgb[1]) ** 2 +
                    (rgb.get("blue", 0) - color_rgb[2]) ** 2) ** 0.5
        if distance < min_distance:
            min_distance = distance
            closest_color_name = color_name
    return closest_color_name
# Sending the images to the API
def recognize_image(image_url: str):
    vision_endpoint = f"https://vision.googleapis.com/v1/images:annotate?key={api_key}"
    request_payload = {
        "requests": [
            {
                "image": {
                    "source": {
                        "imageUri": image_url
                    }
                },
                "features": [
                    {"type": "LABEL_DETECTION", "maxResults": 2},
                    {"type": "TEXT_DETECTION"},
                    {"type": "IMAGE_PROPERTIES"},
                ],
            }
        ]
    }
    response = requests.post(vision_endpoint, json=request_payload)
    if response.status_code == 200:
        return response.json()
    else:
        document.log(f"Request failed with status {response.status_code}: {response.text}")
        response.raise_for_status()
json_result = recognize_image(ec_image)
# Extracting the additional metadata from the API
labels = [
    annotation["description"] for annotation in json_result["responses"][0].get("labelAnnotations", [])[:1]
]
text = [
    annotation["description"] for annotation in json_result["responses"][0].get("textAnnotations", [])[:1]
]
dominant_colors_data = json_result["responses"][0].get("imagePropertiesAnnotation", {}).get("dominantColors", {}).get("colors", [])
dominant_colors = [
    find_closest_color(color["color"]) for color in dominant_colors_data[:1]
]
document.log(f"API returns labels: {labels}")
# Appending the enriched metadata to the document
document.add_meta_data({"labels": labels})
document.add_meta_data({"text": text})
document.add_meta_data({"dominant_colors": dominant_colors})
model.description: A pre-extension which sends all your product content to Google Cloud Vision API and uses the features returned to enrich your indexed content.
model.name: EnrichedMetadata

import string

def getBreadPart(field, fieldtoset):
    #Clean up
    result=''
    content=field
    content=content.replace("-"," ").title()
    parts=content.split('/')
    previous=''
    for part in parts:
        if (part!=''):
            if (previous==''):
                previous = part
                result = previous+';'
            else:
                previous = previous +'|'+part
                result = result + previous+';'
    document.add_meta_data({fieldtoset:result})
    document.log(fieldtoset+' set to: '+result)
    return result

prefix = "https://www.coveo.com"
prefix2 = "http://www."
prefix3 = "https://"
postfix = ".html"
URL=document.get_meta_data_value('clickableuri')[0]
URL=URL.replace(prefix,"")
URL=URL.replace(prefix2,"")
URL=URL.replace(prefix3,"")
URL=URL.replace(postfix,"")
document.log(URL)

res=getBreadPart(URL,'custurlnav')

old_yt = document.get_meta_data_value("ytthumbnailurl")

p = document.get_meta_data_value("scraped_price")[0]
document.log('scraped_price: ' + str(p))

float_p = 0

try:
    if "£" in p:
        p = p.replace(",", "")
        split_p = p.split("£")
        float_p = float(split_p[-1])
    if "€" in p:
        p = p.replace("\xa0", " ")
        p = p.replace(".","")
        split_p = p.split("€")
        float_p = float(split_p[0].replace(",", "."))
except Exception as e:
    log(e, "Error")


document.add_meta_data({"ec_price": float_p})
document.log('ec_price'+' set to: '+ str(float_p))
